      "content": "thanks. one thing i'm seeing in the news is that a lot of experts are saying existential risk isn't just a theory but a very real, immediate danger that we have to take seriously right now. do you think the 'innovation' argument is actually a valid counterpoint to something as serious as human extinction, or is it more of a distraction?",
